			<h2><a href="http://essays.backintyme.biz/item/52" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: African-Americans Also &#8220;Shoot Up Schools&#8221;">African-Americans Also &#8220;Shoot Up Schools&#8221;</a></h2>
			<div class="entry">
				            <article itemscope itemtype="http://nik.io/v1/schema/Article">
      <span itemprop="lastModifiedDate" content="2013-04-14 17:05:51"></span><span itemprop="title" content="African-Americans Also "Shoot Up Schools""></span><span itemprop="categories" content="The Color Line"></span><span itemprop="tags" content=""></span><span itemprop="srcType" content="wordpress.org"></span><span itemprop="permalink" content="http://essays.backintyme.biz/item/52"></span><span id= "wpLogin" itemprop="wpLogin" content=""></span><p align="center"><strong>Essays on the Color Line and the One-Drop Rule</strong><br />
by <a href="http://www.getcited.org/mbrz/11084339">Frank W Sweet</a><br />
September 7, 2009</p>
<p id="fp">A</p>
<p id="sc">ccording to President Obama&#8217;s (now resigned) &#8220;green policy&#8221; advisor Van Jones, &#8220;Only suburban white kids shoot-up schools.&#8221; <a href="http://www.breitbart.tv/van-jones-only-suburbal-white-kids-shoot-up-schools/">See the video.</a></p>
<p>In fact, most school shooters (55 percent) are African Americans. Ever since the federal government made the nation&#8217;s schools death-traps in 1996 by outlawing armed self-defense by administrators, teachers, staff, or students, the rate of incidents has climbed to one school shooting every 60 days. From January 1, 1997 to September 16, 2009 there have been 50 school shootings involving 66 shooters. Of those 66 shooters, 36 were African-American, 19 were Euro-American, and 11 were other (Korean, Philippine, Indian, undetermined). Click on the links in the following table for pictures of the shooters. The fraction of African-American school shooters (53 percent) is higher than the African-American share of any other form of criminal violence.</p>
